text: Dimethylcarbamoyl fluoride is a chemical compound that can be produced by fluorinating the dimethylcarbamoyl chloride with potassium fluoride. It's a colorless liquid that is soluble and stable in water. Dimethylcarbamoyl fluoride is highly toxic because it's a potent cholinesterase inhibitor and is lethal even at low doses. ==See also== *Dimethylcarbamoyl chloride ==References== Category:Acyl fluorides Category:Acetylcholinesterase inhibitors
title: Dimethylcarbamoyl fluoride
